[Jookgaeji site]

149
00:12:14,230 --> 00:12:19,160
[Red commie mark discovery]

150
00:12:19,160 --> 00:12:22,140
[July 25 discovery: Saemaul Angels Tunnel]

151
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:24,980
[Red commie marker discovered]

152
00:12:24,980 --> 00:12:27,630
[Red commie marker discovered]

153
00:12:38,407 --> 00:12:40,533
This is us when we were young.

154
00:12:40,533 --> 00:12:42,202
This is me.

155
00:12:42,202 --> 00:12:43,787
And that's Yang Sun.

156
00:12:43,787 --> 00:12:47,499
And Kim Hyeon Su, who used to live next door.

157
00:12:47,499 --> 00:12:50,903
I hope your hometown energizes you.

158
00:12:53,130 --> 00:12:55,423
And that's Eung Soon.

159
00:12:55,423 --> 00:12:57,885
He was the oldest of us.

160
00:13:01,180 --> 00:13:02,806
What about him?

161
00:13:02,806 --> 00:13:05,350
Does he live here, too?

162
00:13:07,687 --> 00:13:09,537
That's Se Wook.

163
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:11,590
The deceased Lee Se Wook.

164
00:13:13,609 --> 00:13:15,485
Who are you?

165
00:13:24,412 --> 00:13:29,316
Lee Se Wook was also from Black Bridge Valley?

166
00:13:30,935 --> 00:13:33,980
What exactly happened in that village?

167
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:39,676
Before that, I'd like to hear your story.

168
00:13:40,803 --> 00:13:45,165
What did you mean that I was killing people?

169
00:13:46,951 --> 00:13:49,118
Someone's been killing people,

170
00:13:49,119 --> 00:13:51,647
disguising them as accidents.

171
00:13:53,874 --> 00:13:55,968
Lee Se Wook...

172
00:13:57,419 --> 00:13:59,888
was his accomplice.

173
00:14:01,841 --> 00:14:04,050
No way...

174
00:14:04,051 --> 00:14:06,804
The murderer was trying to kill someone today, too.

175
00:14:07,596 --> 00:14:09,314
I think...

176
00:14:11,292 --> 00:14:13,819
you were the target.

177
00:14:19,091 --> 00:14:20,501
But...

178
00:14:21,318 --> 00:14:24,313
how do you know about that?

179
00:14:27,683 --> 00:14:30,294
Did the mountain tell you that, too?

180
00:14:34,748 --> 00:14:37,484
I found out while doing some investigating

181
00:14:37,484 --> 00:14:40,179
after what happened to Lee Se Wook.

182
00:14:42,573 --> 00:14:44,758
All the victims were...

183
00:14:45,409 --> 00:14:47,903
from the Black Bridge Valley.

184
00:14:52,850 --> 00:14:57,104
I'm sure the murderer has some relationship to the village.

185
00:15:02,276 --> 00:15:04,761
Your turn now.

186
00:15:04,761 --> 00:15:07,039
Black Bridge Village...

187
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:11,200
What happened in that village?

188
00:15:11,201 --> 00:15:13,786
I was too young, so I don't remember the details.

189
00:15:13,787 --> 00:15:15,913
But...

190
00:15:15,914 --> 00:15:18,692
I just remember there being many funerals in a row.

191
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:22,629
First, it was my mom,

192
00:15:22,630 --> 00:15:25,340
then Se Wook's dad...

193
00:15:25,341 --> 00:15:28,785
and then my father's was the last one.

194
00:15:30,596 --> 00:15:33,090
How did they die?

195
00:15:35,059 --> 00:15:38,670
I heard my mom and Se Wook's father died in an accident.

196
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,815
My father...

197
00:15:42,733 --> 00:15:44,660
committed suicide.

198
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:50,148
But why...?

199
00:15:50,908 --> 00:15:53,159
I told you.

200
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:55,988
I was too young to remember.

201
00:15:57,915 --> 00:16:00,583
And who would have told the real reason

202
00:16:00,584 --> 00:16:03,503
to such a young child?

203
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:08,716
What about the ghost lights you mentioned?

204
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:11,094
You told me...

205
00:16:11,095 --> 00:16:14,847
that the village disappeared not because of the cable cars or the demolition,

206
00:16:14,848 --> 00:16:17,134
but because of the ghost lights.

207
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:20,979
I always saw a ghost light

208
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:23,281
before something bad happened.

209
00:16:50,050 --> 00:16:51,785
A ghost light...

210
00:16:52,344 --> 00:16:54,287
What exactly was it?

211
00:16:54,287 --> 00:16:58,041
I have no clue what that could be.

212
00:16:58,876 --> 00:17:01,811
My father saw it, too,

213
00:17:01,812 --> 00:17:04,281
but we never found out what it was.

214
00:17:07,651 --> 00:17:09,736
And...

215
00:17:09,737 --> 00:17:12,305
Lee Se Wook?

216
00:17:12,305 --> 00:17:14,532
What was he like?

217
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:17,910
Eung Soon knew him best.

218
00:17:17,911 --> 00:17:22,498
After the village got demolished, I left Jirisan.

219
00:17:22,499 --> 00:17:27,086
Because both my parents passed, I went to live with relatives in Seoul.

220
00:17:27,087 --> 00:17:31,007
I heard Hyeon Su and Yang Sun also left here.

221
00:17:31,008 --> 00:17:36,042
Only Se Wook and Eung Soon remained.

222
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:43,227
They were close from childhood,

223
00:17:43,228 --> 00:17:45,981
so Se Wook must have relied on Eung Soon a lot.

224
00:17:58,570 --> 00:18:01,770
[Police]

225
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:11,040
[The police people can trust and rely on]

226
00:18:11,048 --> 00:18:13,549
How can I help you?

227
00:18:13,550 --> 00:18:16,304
The daily log of the flood that you requested earlier.

228
00:18:16,304 --> 00:18:18,471
Thank you.

229
00:18:18,472 --> 00:18:23,101
Someone who knows the villagers better than anyone else.

230
00:18:23,102 --> 00:18:26,979
He must have well known why and when

231
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:29,024
the victims went to the mountain.

232
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,477
- By the way...
- Yes?

233
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:36,447
I went to Black Bridge Valley on patrol yesterday

234
00:18:36,448 --> 00:18:38,734
and met Senior Kim Sol.

235
00:18:41,078 --> 00:18:44,998
He said you were to meet him there.

236
00:18:45,916 --> 00:18:47,166
That's right.

237
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:50,470
But something urgent came up, so I couldn't go.

238
00:18:54,383 --> 00:18:57,060
Is there anything else I can help you with?

239
00:18:58,720 --> 00:19:00,347
No.

240
00:19:01,331 --> 00:19:03,308
I'll see you later.

241
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:19,112
Have you been hiking these days?

242
00:19:19,783 --> 00:19:22,903
No. I've been busy with work.

243
00:19:25,581 --> 00:19:27,148
I see.

244
00:19:30,590 --> 00:19:35,930
